I just finished reading that book you recommended, the one about the history of maps. It was surprisingly engaging! I never realized how much politics and exploration shaped cartography. Some of the stories about early explorers are pretty wild. I'm always amazed at what they accomplished with such limited tools. Anyway, if you have any other non-fiction recommendations, I'm all ears. I'm trying to read more this year. Let me know what you thought of it if you finished it already! Oh, and did you ever get around to fixing that shelf in your garage? I finally bought a new drill and it made the job so much easier. Sometimes having the right tool really does make all the difference.

